Brazilian oil firm Transpetro said the spill was caused by thieves who broke into a pipeline, causing oil to leak into the Estrela river. The pipeline has been repaired and 70% of the spill has been cleared. But the extent of the damage to wildlife is not yet known. On an oil ship off Angola, life is work and privacy is a luxury As Angola launches its largest ever investment in offshore oil and gas exploration, AFP meets the men and women behind the huge project.